# Kvindo Cloud Provider

The Kvindo Cloud provider lets you manage [Kvindo Cloud](https://cloud.kvindo.com) infrastructure
as code. It talks to the same REST API as the [web console](https://cloud.kvindo.com) and the
[`kc` CLI](https://github.com/Kvindo/kc-cli), so anything you can provision in the console you can
declare in Terraform.

Supported resources include virtual machines (VMs), block volumes, floating IPs, S3 object
storage, Kubernetes clusters and node groups, load balancers, security groups, route tables, VPCs
and VPC peering, VPNs (OpenVPN), managed PostgreSQL, GitLab, monitoring (VictoriaMetrics), billing,
and IAM (users, tokens, access policies).

## Requirements

- [Terraform](https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/downloads) >= 1.0
- A Kvindo Cloud account and an API token (set `KVINDO_TOKEN`, or pass `token` in the provider block)

## Installation

```terraform
terraform {
  required_providers {
    kvindo = {
      source = "kvindo/kvindo"
    }
  }
}
```

